 Thus,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lim_{x\to-\infty}\erf(x)=-\frac{2}{\sqrt{\pi}}\frac{\sqrt{\pi}}{2}=-1.
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Enumerate
The domain of 
\begin_inset Formula $\erf(x)$
\end_inset

 is the whole number line,
 because the integral 
\begin_inset Formula $\int_{0}^{x}\e^{-t^{2}}\,\dl t$
\end_inset

 makes sense for any fixed number 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

.
 On the other hand,
 the range is the interval 
\begin_inset Formula $(-1,1)$
\end_inset

